CIPB_HUNTH - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Acts as a scaffolding protein in the cellulosome. It promotes binding of cellulose to the catalytic domains of the cellulolytic enzymes probably through the binding of the nine repeated domains with dockerin domains present in catalytic subunits of the cellulosome. From Hungateiclostridium thermocellum (Clostridium thermocellum).
